cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.LG

The paper deals with the mechanization of Galois connections, which are a foundational tool in semantics and abstract interpretation. This makes cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) the most likely category, as it deals with the foundations of computer science. The paper also discusses the use of Galois connections in certified programming, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also presents two case studies, one of which deals with static analysis, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the addition of monadic structure to Galois connections, which is related to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the use of reasoning principles not captured by previous mechanization approaches, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
